President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for various positions in the United States Court system. The nominees include Patrick J. Bumatay and Lawrence VanDyke for Circuit Judges on the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit, John W. Holcomb for Judge on the United States District Court for the Central District of California, Knut S. Johnson for Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of California, Steve Kim for Judge on the United States District Court for the Central District of California, Michelle M. Pettit for Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of California, and Thomas Michael O'Connor for United States Marshal for the Southern District of Texas. The nominees have diverse backgrounds and experience in the legal field.